Both of these files will only work when PHP is being run as a module loaded by your webserver; otherwise, PHP doesn't have
access to the request headers. See http://www.php.net/manual/en/function.apache-request-headers.php#74592 for information
on getting access to specific headers when running PHP via CGI.

aprilfools.php:
A full class implementation of DNF header checking, including public static methods testing if users have explicitly or
implicitly opted in or out of April Fools jokes. Licensed under Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 to simplify integration.

do-not-fool.php:
An extremely minimal implementation, designed to be easy to hide in existing code.
